ss=\"fn\">R₁</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The **Schwarz Lemma**: if `f : ℂ → E` is complex analytic\non an open disk with center `c` and a positive radius `R₁`,\nand it sends this disk to a closed ball with center `f c` and radius `R₂`,\nthen the norm of the derivative of `f` at `c` is at most the ratio `R₂ / R₁`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.html#Complex.norm_deriv_le_div_of_mapsTo_ball","kind":"theorem","line":251,"name":"Complex.norm_deriv_le_div_of_mapsTo_ball","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.lean#L251-L259"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.html#Complex.norm_le_norm_of_mapsTo_ball_self\"><span class=\"name\">Complex</span>.<span class=\"name\">norm_le_norm_of_mapsTo_ball_self</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span> → <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hd</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/FDeriv/Defs.html#DifferentiableOn\">DifferentiableOn</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Metric.ball\">Metric.ball</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <span class=\"fn\">R</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h_maps</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.MapsTo\">Set.MapsTo</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Metric.ball\">Metric.ball</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <span class=\"fn\">R</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Metric.closedBall\">Metric.closedBall</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <span class=\"fn\">R</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h₀</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hz</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\">z</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">z</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\">z</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**Alias** of `Complex.norm_le_norm_of_mapsTo_ball`.\n\n---\n\nThe **Schwarz Lemma**.\nLet `f : E → F` be a complex analytic on an open ball with center at the origin.\nIf `f` sends this ball to the closed ball with center `0` of the same radius and `f 0 = 0`,\nthen for any point `z` of this disk we have `‖f z‖ ≤ ‖z‖`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.html#Complex.norm_le_norm_of_mapsTo_ball_self","kind":"theorem","line":241,"name":"Complex.norm_le_norm_of_mapsTo_ball_self","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.lean#L241-L242"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.html#Complex.norm_le_norm_of_mapsTo_ball\"><span clas