**. Let `f : E → F` be a complex analytic function\non an open ball with center `c`.\nIf `f` sends this ball to a closed ball with center `f c` and the same radius,\nthen for any `z` in the former ball we have `dist (f z) (f c) ≤ dist z c`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.html#Complex.dist_le_dist_of_mapsTo_ball_self","kind":"theorem","line":219,"name":"Complex.dist_le_dist_of_mapsTo_ball_self","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.lean#L219-L220"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.html#Complex.dist_le_dist_of_mapsTo_ball\"><span class=\"name\">Complex</span>.<span class=\"name\">dist_le_dist_of_mapsTo_ball</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</sp