>\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hd</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/FDeriv/Defs.html#DifferentiableOn\">DifferentiableOn</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Metric.ball\">Metric.ball</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span> <span class=\"fn\">R₁</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h_maps</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.MapsTo\">Set.MapsTo</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Metric.ball\">Metric.ball</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span> <span class=\"fn\">R₁</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Metric.closedBall\">Metric.closedBall</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">c</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">R₂</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hn</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">c</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.IsLittleO\">=o[</a><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.IsLittleO\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">w</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>) =&gt; <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\">w</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hz</span> : <span class=\"fn\">z</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Metric.ball\">Metric.ball</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span> <span class=\"fn\">R₁</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Dist.dist\">dist</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">z</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">c</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">R₂</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Dist.dist\">dist</a> <span class=\"fn\">z</span> <span class=\"fn\">c</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">R₁</span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `f : E → F` be a complex analytic map\nsending an open ball of radius `R₁` to a closed ball of radius `R₂`.\nIf `f w - f c = o(‖w - c‖ ^ n)`, then for any `z` in the ball in the domain,\nwe have `dist (f z) (f c) ≤ R₂ * (dist z c / R₁) ^ (n + 1)`.\n\nFor `n = 0`, this theorem gives a usual Schwarz lemma,\nsee `dist_le_div_mul_dist_of_mapsTo_ball` below.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.html#Complex.dist_le_mul_div_pow_of_mapsTo_ball_of_isLittleO","kind":"theorem","line":136,"name":"Complex.dist_le_mul_div_pow_of_mapsTo_ball_of_isLittleO","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Schwarz.lean#L136-L181"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Complex.AbsMax","Mathlib.Analysis.Complex.RemovableSingularity"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Analysis.Complex.Schwarz"}